message: I'm getting a kick out the latest @SFWeekly cover, but I do love me some Juxtapoz!
I collect SF Weekly, but I don't actually read it cover to cover. I generally don't read "paper" these days.
I think 7x7 is popular - if not thinning these days.
I'm with @brianball. 7x7 hands down the most informative magazine for upcoming people, places, and things to do in The City.
My observations on MUNI say it is a 50/50 split between People and The Economist.
I love Juxtapoz.  It's distinctly San Fransican.

Thanks so much, @scottholtog @mko @InternetSaant @brianball @splaice (et al)SanFran folks. I will research all your suggested mags/sites. I am helping out #Kickstarter Mission Dolores Mural: 36 Days to Complete a 7-Year Project http://t.co/uYe63wf need to submit for PR opportunities
In San Francisco we read the internet
